Cell.Text: [S] By the Hist, more taxes. I'll take care of this, don't worry.
[S] So the Jarl's raising taxes again. Great.
[S] More taxes? It never ends.
[S] Oh, lovely. Taxes. Fine. I'll make sure the money is raised when the time comes.
[S] Taxes? We'll pay them, but don't expect gratitude.
[S] The Jarl is demanding more taxes? Fine. They'll be paid.
[S] Taxes are being raised, again? As if things weren't bad enough.
[S] The Jarl will get my taxes when the time comes.
[S] More taxes? Just what I need. Anything else you'd like to do to ruin my day?
[S] Taxes? I suppose the store can afford to pay a little more.
[S] More tribute? You'd think the Jarl was a stronghold chief who can't get enough deer for his feasting.
[S] So the Jarl wants more money? I suppose I can just pull some gold out of thin air. Idiot.
[S] The Jarl wants more from me? I already give so much.
[S] Oh, taxes are being raised? I'll see what I can do.
[S] Great. More taxes. They'll be paid.
[S] Taxes? They'll be paid.
[S] The Jarl's raising taxes again? Divines have mercy.
[S] Oh, wonderful. My taxes are being raised. Because life wasn't hard enough, it seems.
[S] Taxes are being raised. Don't like this, but they'll be paid.
[S] Oh, isn't this nice? A letter saying I have to pay even more taxes. What a fortunate day this is.
[S] Taxes are being raised? It'll be hard, but they'll be paid.
[S] More taxes, huh? They'll be paid.
[S] Jarl wants to raise my taxes, huh? Great. Just great.
[S] So the Jarl is raising my taxes? I'll see what I can do.
[S] The Jarl is growing fat on my gold. Oh well. Rather a fat chief than a weak one.
[S] Raising my taxing, huh? Just when I thought the Jarl and I were going to be friends.
[S] By the Divines, more taxes. I'll do what I can to pay them.

Node.Caption: Favor050QuestGiverBranchTopic: Is there anything I can do for ?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Good work. I appreciate someone who's reliable. Here, something from the Jarl's stores.
<<Shared>> The Hold thanks you. Here, this is for you.
<<Shared>> I've seen worse work. Go along now, I've things to do.
<<Shared>> Good to hear. Now if you'll excuse me, I'm a busy man.
<<Shared>> Good, good. Glad to see people doing things for the Hold.
<<Shared>> Yes, yes. The Hold thanks you, and so on and so forth.
<<Shared>> The Hold thanks you for your service.
<<Shared>> Not bad. Usually my people can't find their own hands.
<<Shared>> Some good news for once.
[S] I need you to deliver this tax notice to a merchant in my Hold. Don't worry about the money, just hand them the letter.
[S] A simple task. Deliver this tax notice to a merchant in one of my towns. No need to pick up any money now. It'll come later.
[S] Let's see if you can handle delivering this tax notice.
[S] I need a tax notice delivered. Remind the merchants in my Hold that guards aren't free.
[S] These petty shop-keepers need to be reminded who they owe their taxes to. Send this notice out.
[S] This tax notice needs to be sent out.
[S] There's some tax notices that need to go out. Here, deliver this one for me.
[S] Damn merchants need to remember whose land they're on. Slap this tax notice in their faces.
[S] I need someone to serve a tax notice to the merchants in my Hold. Just make sure it reaches them, and then it's their problem.
[S] I hereby grant you permission to purchase property in the city. Talk to my steward if you're interested. | And take this. A gift from the Jarl's personal armory.
[S] As a reward, take this. A gift from my personal armory.
